100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 14, 1925, tensions rose in the Middle East as the British government announced plans to establish a new administrative framework in Palestine, sparking mixed reactions among Jewish and Arab communities. In Europe, the League of Nations continued to grapple with issues of disarmament, as nations sought to stabilize post-war relations. Meanwhile, the United States faced ongoing debates over Prohibition, with calls for reform growing louder amid widespread enforcement challenges.
